e decline of European power and the ascendency of the USA; two World Wars; the Wall Street crash; communism and fascism. Through the eyes of Arlt, Benedetti, Campodónico, Cortázar, De Castro, Denevi, Fernández, Marechal, Mariani, Martínez Estrada, Onetti and Ricci, we observe life on both sides of the River Plate, as the two countries succumb to polarisation, repression and, eventually, military dictatorship. This is the twentieth century, viewed by a bewildered, frequently anguished participant: the person at the next desk. PAUL R. JORDAN lectures in Hispanic Studies at the University of Sheffield.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aArgentine prose literaturexHistory and criticismy20th century. 0aArgentine prose literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aLiterature and societyzArgentina. 0aLiterature and societyzUruguay. 0aSocial change in literature. 0aUruguayan prose literaturexHistory and criticismy20th century. 0aUruguayan prose literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 4aHispanic Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Spanish & Portuguese.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846154478423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846154478/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles